news.title: Pune: Building permission department may not remain cash cow next fiscal
news.para: The commissioner’s budget reduced the revenue target of the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) department substantially to Rs1,400 crore for the 2022-23 financial year.

news.title: Demand for satellite, boutique offices surge post pandemic
news.para: Several factors including caution towards capital expenditure, need for flexibility in lease terms and allowing mobility to workforce as organisations await more clarity in business conditions and workplace strategies are helping push the demand for satellite offices.

news.title: Delhi development authority's survey in 87 slums to help find them new homes
news.para: Around 20 lakh people live in 677 slum clusters out of which 490 are on land belonging to DDA and the central government.

news.title: Post-sop home registrations losing steam in Kolkata
news.para: In February 2022, only 1,593 property sales deeds were registered, less than 4,595 registrations that were done in February 2021 when the sops weren’t there and even less than February 2020, when 3,642 deeds were registered.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body plans mandatory third party structural audit of all highrises
news.para: Currently, there is no provision for a structural audit in the UP Apartment Act, and developers get the same done by auditors of their choice for seeking completion certificates from the GDA.

news.title: Takeover of DLF areas not before March 31: Gurugram civic body
news.para: According to a recent report submitted by the developer to the Municipal Corporation of Gurugram (MCG), nearly 88% of the road resurfacing work is complete in DLF-1, 72% in DLF-2 and 80% in DLF-3.

news.title: Suncity RWA can't charge upkeep fee: Gurugram district registrar
news.para: The district registrar further said the RWA, which was registered under the Haryana Registration and Regulation of Societies Act, 2012, doesn’t have the right to collect these charges as the society is a residential plotted colony approved by the department of town and country planning under the Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Act, 1975.

news.title: Maharashtra clears property tax waiver for houses of up to 500 sq ft in Mumbai
news.para: The exemption will be implemented with retrospective effect from January 1, 2022.

news.title: Bank consortium informs SC of Rs 300 crore infusion to complete Amrapali projects
news.para: At the outset, the bench was informed by senior advocate N Venkataramani, who has been appointed as court receiver, that Bank of Baroda has infused Rs 300 crore while other five banks of the consortium are in process of releasing the funds.

news.title: British house prices rising at the fastest rate since 2007: Halifax
news.para: That brought the average price of a house in Britain to 278,123 pounds ($367,511), up 10.8% on a year ago and marking the fastest annual growth rate since June 2007.

news.title: Shriram Housing loan-book grows 45% to cross Rs 5,000-crore so far this fiscal
news.para: Had it not been for the third wave and the resultant curbs on our operations, which impacted collections, the AUM would have already crossed the Rs 5000-crore-mark in December as planned. This also will impact the annual target of Rs 5,500 crore of live loans, and we should now be closing the year with Rs 5,200-5,300 crore of AUM, said Ravi Subramanian, MD and chief executive.

news.title: An uncertain future looms over residents of unauthorised colonies in Dehradun
news.para: Locals say that more than 75 families live in the area. Gradually, permanent structures are also coming up in these colonies.

news.title: Curated Living Solutions plans to set up $200-million fund to build co-living centres
news.para: Curated Living Solutions currently has 7,500 beds operational at its co-living centres in Bengaluru and Pune, of which 4,000 beds are for students, 2,000 for industrial workers and 1,500 for working professionals.

news.title: Chandigarh Housing Board earns Rs 223 crore revenue in FY22
news.para: The Chandigarh Housing Board has also failed in its expenditure target, spending Rs 114.01 crore out of Rs 202.54 it had anticipated.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers files DRHP for Rs 500 crore IPO
news.para: The proceeds from its fresh issuance worth Rs 315 crore for the repayment or prepayment of borrowings, in full or part of all or certain borrowings for Suraj Estate Developers and its subsidiary, Rs 45 crore for acquisition of land or land development rights besides general corporate purposes.
